title: App keeps crashing
text:
Every time I try to clear searched locations the app automatically crashes each time. I’ve already cleared the application data and even reinstalled the app and this still happens.

Also, PLEASE PLEASE add the ability to report incidents while using CarPlay, similar to Waze. Makes no sense that this function doesn’t exist already in 2024. The whole point of CarPlay and even AndroidAuto is to increase safety while driving and prevent the use of our phones but Google Maps doesn’t adhere to this by making it necessary to report incidents on our phone.

title: ugh, downhill
text: interesting watching the quality steadily decline of this app and the directions provided, from increasing usability problems to missing information and outright weird directions. I’m late for an appointment standing waiting for a subway on the long way round in Taipei. In Germany a local said sure, let’s use the stupid directions when pulling out Google maps. Google has lost its way, not that it ever found it, just is clearly aiming for something other than compatibility with human living beyond its stock price. And even that priority it’s debatable how successfully it’s navigating.

title: Maps malfunction of contributor’s photos and reviews
text: Google maps is my go to app when it comes to navigating outside cities. I’ve been a contributor by posting reviews and photos since 2018 as a way of saying thank you to other contributors. The app is now glitching in this Feild as well, I’ve noticed 0 views on photos posted and found other contributors on a forum that are complaining about incoherent responses from the Google maps section about this issue. Whatever algorithm they applied should be changed, I too have sent past emails that fell on deaf ears. This review is dedicated to them because other platforms don’t work.

title: Auto Reroute to "Best" Route
text:
I find it beyond frustrating that the route that I chose on my way home kept getting usurped by routes that google felt was the best route because it was fastest. And so i went to settings to hopefully allow myself to not have that happen anymore to find that that is not something to be turned on or off. 

I dont think the route should automatically update, if I don't agree to the new route with one of my actions then i shouldn't be put on it, or i should have the option to not have my routes controlled like that. 

Gonna probably try another gps app and hope that i have more agency there

title: Used to be great but now unusable
text: I used to use this app for navigation, but recently the app literally had me going on a toll road and then getting off , then turning around and getting back on the toll road. When I clearly could have saved time and money by going the opposite direction and not getting on the toll road at all. Does Google profit when their app sends on toll roads unnecessarily. Once Google Maps also had no clue where certain addresses are actually located and had me going in circles several times until I had to pull over and ask someone for directions. The app also crashes constantly at some of the most inconvenient times. Google Maps used to be great, but it’s just completely unusable now. Try using Apple Maps or Waze instead.
